boardroom.%3Cp%3EShannon%20Fagan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECEOs%20face%20pressure%20from%20investors%20to%20enhance%20their%20AI%20strategies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestor%20demand%20for%20AI%20adoption%20surged%20from%2068%25%20to%2090%25%20from%20Q4%202024%20to%20Q1%202025%2C%20according%20to%20KPMG.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20investor%20told%20BI%20there's%20no%20board%20of%20a%20VC-backed%20startup%20that%20isn't%20discussing%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EExecutives%2C%20investors%2C%20and%20boards%20are%20united%20on%20one%20thing%3A%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-insecure-about-ai-strategy-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenterprise%20AI%20company%20Dataiku%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20a%20survey%20that%20showed%20that%20CEOs%20are%20putting%20pressure%20on%20themselves%2C%20and%20each%20other%2C%20to%20ramp%20up%20their%20AI%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20new%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkpmg-trust-in-ai-study-2025-how-employees-use-ai-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKPMG%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20some%20of%20the%20heat%20is%20coming%20from%20investors.%20Investor%20pressure%20to%20adopt%20AI%20has%20jumped%20from%2068%25%20to%2090%25%20from%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024%20to%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202025%2C%20according%20to%20the%20firm's%20survey%20of%20130%20executives%20from%20a%20mix%20of%20public%20and%20private%20companies%20with%20over%20%241%20billion%20in%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-ai-mckinsey-bcg-deloitte-pwc-kpmg-chatbots-ai-tools-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKPMG's%20head%20of%20ecosystems%20Todd%20Lohr%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20he%20expects%20investors%20to%20double%20down%20more%2C%20potentially%20driving%20a%20rise%20in%20activism.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20signal%20of%20'change%20is%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20come%2C'%20especially%20if%20you're%20not%20moving%20fast%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20going%20to%20be%20others%20that%20are%20going%20to%20move%20your%20hand%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELohr%20said%20board%20members%2C%20too%2C%20are%20becoming%20more%20attuned%20to%20AI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20speeches%20for%20boards%20and%20board%20members%2C%20and%20they're%20getting%20pretty%20deep%20on%20the%20technology%20because%20they%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20asking%20the%20right%20questions%20for%20how%20it's%20going%20to%20disrupt%20their%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20venture%20capitalists%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20are%20actively%20driving%20their%20portfolio%20companies%20to%20deploy%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20working%20with%20our%20portfolio%20companies%20to%20incorporate%20GenAI%20features%20into%20their%20product%20portfolios%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsapphire-investor-jai-das-startups-trends-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJai%20Das%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20president%20and%20partner%20at%20enterprise%20technology%20firm%20Sapphire%20Ventures%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20a%20generational%20shift%2C%20and%20companies%20that%20don't%20embrace%20it%20in%20a%20big%20way%20will%20be%20history%20footnotes%20versus%20becoming%20companies%20of%20consequence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaria%20Palma%2C%20general%20partner%20at%20Freestyle%20Capital%2C%20said%20the%20firm%20has%20been%20having%20discussions%20with%20all%20its%20portfolio%20companies%20on%20how%20they%20are%20integrating%20AI.%20It's%20also%20hosting%20a%20series%20of%20%26quot%3Boptional%20sessions%20on%20AI's%20potential%20to%20improve%20workflows%20across%20various%20departments%2C%20like%20engineering%20or%20marketing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20to%20BI%20by%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20Palma's%20thesis%20is%20that%20companies%20should%20have%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20peripheral%20vision%26quot%3B%20so%20they%20can%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20tools%20competitors%20are%20deploying.%20%26quot%3BAdopting%20AI%20in%20your%20company%20won't%20guarantee%20its%20survival.%20But%20the%20lack%20of%20it%3F%20That%20will%20guarantee%20to%20put%20your%20company%20at%20a%20huge%20disadvantage%2C%20and%20ultimately%20place%20it%20on%20a%20path%20toward%20extinction%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20though%2C%20companies%20are%20scrambling%20to%20save%20face.%20They're%20applying%20AI%20features%20as%20a%20quick%20fix%20rather%20than%20analyzing%20where%20they%20can%20achieve%20real%20gains%2C%20founders%20of%20companies%20developing%20those%20AI%20features%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20results%20in%20an%20%26quot%3BAI%20arms%20race%20that%20creates%20real%20risks%2C%26quot%3B%20Florian%20Douetteau%2C%20Dataiku's%20CEO%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20a%20unified%20strategy%20across%20the%20business%2C%20organizations%20expose%20themselves%20to%20chaos%3A%20siloed%20experimentation%20of%20point%20solutions%2C%20unmonitored%20AI%20application%20usage%2C%20data%20leakage%2C%20cost%20overruns%2C%20and%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Douetteau%20said.%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20raw%20power%2C%20and%20it%20can%20only%20work%20to%20drive%20measurable%20business%20results%20if%20it%20is%20controlled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDarren%20Louie%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20Proof%20%E2%80%94%20a%20platform%20for%20digital%20identity%20and%20verifications%20%E2%80%94%20echoed%20the%20idea.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestor%20expectations%20are%20understandably%20rising%2C%20so%20businesses%20are%20under%20growing%20pressure%20to%20demonstrate%20ROI%20on%20their%20AI%20initiatives%2C%20but%20many%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20serious%20and%20valid%20concerns%20about%20compliance%20and%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Louie%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20board%2C%20spending%20on%20software%20has%20accelerated%20among%20Global%202000%20enterprises%20in%20the%20last%20two%20quarters%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-venture-market-is-surprisingly-rabid-says-investor-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFirstMark%20Capital's%20Matt%20Turck%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Within%20that%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%20increase%26quot%3B%20in%20spend%20on%20AI%20tooling%20and%20applications%20as%20companies%20move%20from%20consulting%20projects%20and%20proof%20of%20concepts%20to%20deploying%20AI%2C%20Turck%20told%20BI%20via%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20discussions%20about%20AI%20are%20happening%20constantly%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20an%20investor%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20any%20board%20of%20VC-backed%20startups%20where%20there%20isn't%20a%20current%20conversation%20on%20using%20AI%20throughout%20the%20company%20to%20increase%20efficiency%20across%20functions%20like%20development%2C%20sales%2C%20marketing%2C%20etc%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%2C%20though%2C%20is%20whether%20the%20Trump%20Administration's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-business-reaction-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweeping%20new%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20change%20things%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Btariff%20nonsense%20is%20particularly%20painful%20because%20it%20may%20(or%20may%20not)%20have%20stopped%20that%20trend%20%E2%80%94%20we'll%20see%20what%20the%20Q2%20numbers%20look%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20Turck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestors-pressuring-companies-to-get-serious-about-ai-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E